    "body": "I didn't notice the term `directory` , I tried with file and worked\r\n```\r\n♥->copy -Recurse -Path .\\t.log -Include *.* -Verbose -Force -Destination C:\\Temp\\ -WhatIf \r\n\r\nWhat if: Performing the operation \"Copy File\" on target \"Item: C:\\Windows\\Temp\\testcopy\\t.log Destination: C:\\Temp\\t.log\".\r\n```\r\n\r\nand doesn't work for directory as you mentioned. And notice that the exclusion issue applies for both directory and path.\r\n\r\n```\r\n♥->copy -Recurse -Path .\\t.log -Exclude t* -Verbose -Force -Destination C:\\Temp\\ -WhatIf\r\n\r\n♥->\r\n```",
